OL,6,F"At that particular moment I am quite
OL,7,Fsatisfied that the red mist descended
OL,8,Fand, partly affected by alcohol, you
OL,9,Fstomped out of the lounge. You stormed
OL,10,Finto the kitchen, you got a knife and
OL,11,Fyou were intending to kill him.
OL,13,F"You lured him into the hallway and
OL,14,Fthen repeatedly stabbed him."
OL,16,FHiggins left Mr Eaton on the floor as
OL,17,Fhe went outside and told a neighbour:
OL,18,F"Best ring an ambulance. I have just
OL,19,Fstabbed my mate. He was doing my
OL,20,Ff***ing head in."
